<TEXT>
<P>
 "The Swimmers" (photographed by Gregg Segal, Aug. 14) brought back memories of 
growing up in Los Angeles in the early 1940s.During the summer, a friend and I 
would cut lawns and clean yards in the morning to earn a dollar between us. 
We'd then pedal our bicycles to Harvard Playground and swim all afternoon, for 
a nickel if you were 11 or under, a dime for those over 12. And I learned to 
swim there. A set of lessons cost 25 cents. 
</P>
<P>
 ED SCHLOSSMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 
</P>
