</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PRAYERS FOR THE DEAD by Dennis Vannatta (White Pine Press: $14; 194 pp., 
paperback original). Dennis Vannatta's stories follow the Workman family from 
1900 through the present day. The son of one of Custer's soldiers, John Workman 
takes his family from their comfortable Pennsylvania home to seek greater 
opportunities in the West. But the vast emptiness of the prairie daunts him, 
and he settles in the tiny hamlet of Sunday's Hollow in Missouri. Workman's 
descendants lead bleak lives, struggling to scratch a living from the scanty 
soil of the Ozarks. Vannatta's spare prose suggests a developing talent, rather 
than a mature one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Book Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
