</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 THE LAND OF THE INCAS photographs by Hans Silverstein, text by Jacques 
Soustelle, translated from the French by Jane Breton (Thames & Hudson: $19.95; 
unpaginated). Soustelle's brief text traces the later history of the Inca 
empire, noting that Pizarro's conquest was facilitated by a murderous civil 
war. Silverstein's glorious photographs show life continuing in the shadows of 
monolithic ruins devoid of the exuberant decorations of Meso-American art. The 
often handsome faces of the people reveal the toll the high altitudes exact. 
</P>
</TEXT>
