<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Mariachi (Cinemax Thursday at 4:40 a.m.) is Robert Rodriguez's sly and 
hilarious 1992 comedy starring Carloes Gallardo in the title role. He is an 
itinerant musician who happens into a Mexican border town only to be mistaken 
for a hit man. 
</P>
<P>
 Cabeza de Vaca (KCET Saturday at 9 p.m.) is Nicolas Echeverria's stunning 
anti-imperialist telling of an ill-fated 16th-Century Spanish voyage of 
exploration to Mexico and part of the United States. Juan Diego stars in this 
1990 Mexican film. 
</P>
<P>
 The Exterminating Angel (El Angel Exterminador) (KCET Saturday at 11 p.m.) is 
one of Luis Bunuel's most inspired attacks on bourgeois morality; the guests at 
a swanky dinner party find themselves unable to leave -- ever. Silvia Pinal 
stars. Made in Mexico in 1962. 
</P>
</TEXT>
