<HEADLINE>
<P>
HE AND 'SHE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If "She TV" is supposed to be "about and for women," why are 11 of the 14 
writers listed male? Perhaps this is the reason so many of its sketches portray 
actresses in various stages of undress. Women viewers crave comedy from a 
female perspective; so far, "She TV" has fallen short. 
</P>
<P>
 Kate Nelson, Van Nuys 
</P>
<P>
 Editor's Note: An ABC publicist for "She TV" reports that there are 13 writers 
on the show, 9 of whom are male. 
</P>
