NEW RELEASES; IN BRIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Leonard Feather 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * * * 1/2 GENE HARRIS QUARTET, "Funky Gene's," Concord Jazz. Here are four 
master chefs who cook as one.Blessed with a long collective track record, 
pianist Harris works tightly with the admirable guitarist Ron Eschete, Luther 
Hughes on bass and Paul Humphrey. There are a couple of agreeable ballads, but 
the accent is on blues: a blues for Basie, a blues by Basie, "Ahmad's Blues." 
Harris always knows the exact tempo for each tune: "Nice and Easy" could well 
have been the title track. 
</P>
