<P>
CRITIC'S PICK: 'MADE IN AMERICA' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Whoopi Goldberg and Ted Danson's romance proved fleeting, but it gave a 
terrific charge to this lively and entertaining 1993 romantic comedy.Goldberg 
plays the successful owner of a Berkeley bookstore devoted to African culture 
and the single mother to a pretty 17-year-old (Nia Long). When Long discovers 
that she was conceived via a sperm bank donation, she becomes determined to 
find the unknown donor-father -- who turns out to be the San Francisco Bay 
Area's gaudiest, hardest-selling car dealer (Danson). Beeath a raucous surface, 
"Made in America" actually has much to reveal about the multicultural society 
in which we live (Cinemax Saturday at 6 p.m.). Kevin Thomas 
