<HEADLINE>
<P>
RE-VERSAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 May I recommend a Pope in the eye with a sharp stick for permitting your 
correspondent to get away with last Sunday's Letters page misquotation of the 
18th Century's most particular wit. 
</P>
<P>
 Here's the way it usually goes: 
</P>
<P>
 Vice is a monster of so frightful mien,  
</P>
<P>
 As, to be hated, needs but to be seen;  
</P>
<P>
 Yet seen too oft, familiar with her face,  
</P>
<P>
 We first endure, then pity, then embrace.  
</P>
<P>
 Hair-splitting academic snit aside, I'm glad to see printed before the eyes of 
millions -- well, several tens of thousands -- even partially accurate words 
from a guy who understood what moral venom was all about. I wonder if Rush 
Limbaugh, just before he heats up the mike, reminds himself, "I am getting into 
the ring with Mr. Pope"? 
</P>
<P>
 Naah!  
</P>
<P>
 DAVID WILSON 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
</P>
