<P>
BRIEFLY: LANDMARK: TOWER REDEDICATION SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Hollywood landmark, damaged in the Jan. 17 earthquake, will be replaced atop 
a Hollywood Boulevard office building in a rededication ceremony at 2 p.m. on 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Leaning Dome," a 1932 Art Deco cupola on the 95-foot-high office tower, 
suffered major damage to its steel-and-glass frame. 
</P>
<P>
 The tower, known as the eastern gateway to Hollywood, houses the offices of 
Johns + Gorman Films, the company that provided the nearly $80,000 for the 
cupola's repair. 
</P>
