<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEARN ABOUT STATE PROGRAMS TO HELP BUYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The state of California just might be able to help you buy your first home. 
</P>
<P>
 Find out how at the Los Angeles Times' Low-Down Home Loan Expo to be held from 
10 a.m. to 4 p.m. on Saturday, Sept. 24, at the Burbank Hilton Convention 
Center, 2500 Hollywood Way, Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
 Learn about loan programs from the California Housing Finance Agency (CHFA), 
including a 3% mortgage and a new "Generation Link" program that lets parents 
use the equity in their home to help their children with a down payment. 
</P>
<P>
 And the California Public Employees Retirement System (CalPERS) offers a 5% 
down program and a no-down option for members who work for state government and 
meet other qualifying criteria. 
</P>
<P>
 CHFA and CalPERS representatives, as well as experts on many other government 
and commercial loan programs, will be on hand to explain their mortgages. The 
expo also will feature question-and-answer panel discussions and exhibitor 
booths. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost of the all-day consumer education event is $5, but clip the discount 
coupon in the ad in today's Real Estate section and save $2. To get more 
details about the Expo, call TimesLine at 808-8463 and press star 9420 at the 
prompt. Or check the ad on page K2. 
</P>
