<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: COLOR IT FALL IN CALIFORNIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Although leaf-peepers often think they have to go East to see spectacular fall 
color, some of California's finest fall colors can usually be found in the 
historic Gold Rush towns of Grass Valley and Nevada City and along the 160-mile 
Yuba-Donner Scenic Byway, a looped route that goes through the Tahoe National 
Forest. 
</P>
<P>
 Peak color weeks are difficult to predict, but tourism sources say mid-October 
to early November is usually the most colorful period. Color tour maps are 
available and visitors may call ahead to check conditions.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Grass Valley/Nevada County Chamber of Commerce 
(800-655-4667) or the Nevada City Chamber (800-655-NJOY). 
</P>
</TEXT>
