<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: CAJUN CELEBRATION IN LOUISIANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Festivals Acadiens, a celebration of Cajun and zydeco music, Cajun and 
Creole food and native crafts, marks its 18th anniversary Friday, Saturday and 
Sunday in Lafayette, the heart of French Louisiana. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, which draws about 100,000 visitors, is actually a combination of 
several festivals, including the Festival de Musique Acadienne, which began as 
a three-hour concert in 1974 and now offers nonstop music over the three days. 
</P>
<P>
 For a festival schedule, call the Lafayette Convention and Visitors 
Commission, (800) 346-1958. For fax information, call (800) 8-VIS-FAX, Ext. 
650. 
