<HEADLINE>
<P>
MICHIO SUZUKI; U.S. HEALTH OFFICIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michio (Mike) Suzuki, director of the Office of Policy Coordination and 
Analysis of the Administration on Aging for the U.S. Department of Health and 
Human Services, died of a heart attack Wednesday in a Rockfille, Md., 
hospital.He was 65. 
</P>
<P>
 Before moving to Washington in 1972, Suzuki was instrumental in 
re-establishing Shonien: Japanese Children's Home and Child Welfare Center in 
Los Angeles. The center had been closed with the internment of Southern 
California Japanese Americans during World War II. Suzuki was among the 
internees. 
</P>
<P>
 He had also been chief of social services for the California Department of 
Social Welfare. 
</P>
</TEXT>
