<P>
DRIVER CRASHES INTO OWN HOUSE, HURTS CHILD INSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 2-year-old girl was injured when her family's car crashed through the 
kitchen wall of the house, pinning the youngster between the vehicle and a 
couch. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident was reported shortly before 7 a.m. Friday at 12692 Willowood 
Avenue when Tuych Duc Lai was attempting to park the car in the driveway, 
police said.When Lai's foot hit the accelerator, the car lurched forward at a 
high rate of speed and smashed through the wall. 
</P>
<P>
 The man's daughter, Minh Lai, was struck inside the house and pinned by the 
1989 Thunderbird. Police said she suffered a cut on her head and bruises on her 
face. 
</P>
<P>
 She was admitted to UCI Medical Center Friday morning and released Saturday. 
Her mother, Tsao Lai, said Saturday that the child was feeling better but was 
suffering from a fever. 
</P>
<P>
 Tsao Lai said her husband was "feeling very bad" about the accident. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the child's injuries, the accident caused $12,000 in damages to 
the structure and its contents. 
</P>
<P>
 No criminal charges were filed in connection with the incident. 
</P>
