<HEADLINE>
<P>
CYPRESS MAN SOUGHT IN TWO ROBBERIES ARRESTED AT AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 20-year-old man suspected of committing two robberies and shooting a man in 
the head during one of them was arrested at Los Angeles International Airport 
Saturday as he stepped off a plane from Tucson, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Fidel Gutierrez of Cypress was arrested following a two-month 
investigation by La Palma police, said Sgt. Ed Ethell. 
</P>
<P>
 Gutierrez, described by authorities as a member of a Hawaiian Gardens gang, is 
suspected of being one of two men who robbed a 7-Eleven on June 26 of an 
undisclosed amount of cash. 
</P>
<P>
 Ethell said that as Gutierrez and his accomplice left the store, they fired a 
shot at the store clerk as he attempted to write down their license plate. The 
clerk was not hit, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gutierrez is also a suspect in the Aug. 3 robbery of a Rockview Dairy located 
across the street from the convenience store. 
</P>
<P>
 During the second robbery, a man servicing a California Lottery machine inside 
the dairy was shot in the head but his injuries were not life-threatening, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both businesses are located at the intersection of Crescent and Moody streets. 
</P>
<P>
 Gutierrez was being held at Buena Park City Jail on suspicion of attempted 
homicide and robbery, police said. 
</P>
