<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAYLOR GETS 35 POINTS -- IN FIRST QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Baylor scored 35 points in the first quarter and went on to defeat San Jose 
State, 54-20, Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bears (2-0) scored through the air, on the ground, off interceptions and 
blocked punts and even a safety. 
