<HEADLINE>
<P>
COSTA, MIAMI CRUISE PAST ARIZONA STATE; NONCONFERENCE: QUARTERBACK PASSES FOR 
295 YARDS AND FOUR TOUCHDOWNS IN 47-10 VICTORY. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Frank Costa passed for a career-high 295 yards and four touchdowns Saturday 
night and fifth-ranked Miami feasted on first-half turnovers to run away from 
Arizona State, 47-10. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams had never met, but Miami had struck out in three previous trips to 
Sun Devil Stadium.The Hurricanes (2-0) lost in the 1985, 1987 and 1994 Fiesta 
Bowls, absorbing a stinging 29-0 defeat at the hands of Arizona last New Year's 
Day. 
</P>
<P>
 That defeat raised questions whether the proud dynasty was in decline and 
prompted Coach Dennis Erickson to guarantee a victory over Arizona State. His 
Hurricanes wasted little time making good, taking advantage of three fumble 
recoveries and two interceptions to build a 33-10 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Costa completed nine passes in last week's 56-0 victory over Georgia Southern, 
and the Hurricanes scored six touchdowns on the ground. Against a stronger 
opponent, Costa went to a modest passing game that featured short passes, which 
his receivers stretched into long scores. 
</P>
<P>
 Jammi German scored from 56 and 49 yards out on a play called the "middle 
screen," a slant inside to the wide receiver about five yards downfield. German 
put Miami ahead, 6-3, with his first catch, turning outside to beat covering 
linebackers and cutting back inside to outrun the secondary. 
</P>
<P>
 His second touchdown made the score 40-10 with 8:41 to play in the third 
quarter, and Erickson pulled Costa. 
</P>
<P>
 Costa also completed touchdown passes of 10 yards to Chris T. Jones and 53 
yards to tailback Jonathan Harris, who caught Arizona State in a blitz and 
raced to the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
 James Stewart scored on nine- and one-yard runs, and Danyell Ferguson made a 
three-yard touchdown run. 
</P>
</TEXT>
