<HEADLINE>
<P>
1994 PREP PREVIEW / GIRLS' CROSS-COUNTRY; SIX TEAMS TO WATCH; ESPERANZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: Rich Medellin (fifth year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: Empire League champions; undefeated in league dual meets; runners-up at 
the Orange County Championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Carrie Caulkins, Sr.; Katie De Freise, So.; Courtney Pugmire, 
Sr.; Chantelle Rodrigues, Sr.; Crystal Smith, Jr.; Jenny Titus, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Joanna Ho, So.; Inshirah Jones, Sr.; Heather Perrin, Jr.; 
Jennifer Walters, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: The Aztecs are on a mission this season, having lost the Orange 
County Championships title to Edison on the sixth-runner rule last year, then 
failing to advance as a team to the CIF State finals. Medellin has one of the 
state's strongest trio leading the way again. Caulkins, Pugmire and Titus each 
advanced to the State Division I finals last season. Caulkins, who finished 
fourth at the county meet, earned Times Orange County first-team honors. 
Pugmire and Titus, who finished ninth and 11th at the county race, garnered 
second-team honors. Perrin was the Aztecs' leading 400-meter runner in track 
last spring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
