<HEADLINE>
<P>
1994 PREP PREVIEW / GIRLS' CROSS-COUNTRY; SIX TEAMS TO WATCH; DANA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: Ron Buchheim (11th year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: South Coast League champions; third at the Southern Section Division 
I-AA finals; fifth at the Orange County Championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Kim Beck, Sr.; Bree Denison, Jr.; Laura Kroninger, So.; Sidney 
Leonard, So.; Jordi Manley, Sr.; Kristin More, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Casey Bray, So; Heidi Peterson, Jr.; Kelly Reed, Jr.; Kelly 
Spears, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: With the top six runners returning from last season's team, the 
Dolphins are ready to move up to the state's elite level. Leonard finished 
among the top 20 at the Orange County Championships last year, while Beck 
placed 30th. In the South Coast League finals, Kroninger, Denison and More 
finished 5-6-7 to help secure the championship. More also complimented that 
finish with an 11th place in the section race. Manley complements one of the 
county's deepest teams, and Buchheim has a wealth of talent from which to 
choose to fill the one remaining spot. "I've had a real run of talent over the 
last few years, so that's helping matters a lot," said Buchheim, who is in his 
third year at the Dana Hills helm after a three-year hiatus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
