<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALVARY CHAPEL ROLLS OVER HORIZON, 28-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICHARD MELKONIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Calvary Chapel Eagles kicked off their season with an impressive 28-0 
victory over San Diego Horizon on Saturday at the first Fellowship Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 All-purpose wide receiver Mark Echan was the Eagles' workhorse, scoring two 
touchdowns and gaining 127 yards in 18 carries.Echan also led all receivers 
with 66 yards on four receptions. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Waylan Kruse played an error-free game, passing for two touchdowns 
that covered 17 and 19 yards. The Eagles' offensive line beat down the 
Panthers, providing Kruse with ample time to locate his downfield receivers. 
</P>
<P>
 The stingy Eagle defense allowed only 13 passing yards on three receptions, 
and had numerous gang tackles against the Panthers behind the line of 
scrimmage. 
</P>
<P>
 The game broke open in the second quarter when the Eagles, who had scored on 
an Echan three-yard touchdown run, recovered their own kickoff at the Panthers' 
19-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 It took Kruse only one play to find wide receiver Aaron Fountain, who made a 
diving reception in the corner of the end zone. The two-point conversion 
attempt was successful as Echan caught Kruse's pass to give the Eagles a 21-0 
halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Kruse threw a 17-yard touchdown pass to Echan in the third quarter to seal the 
victory. RICHARD MELKONIAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
