<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; MT. SAN ANTONIO, FULLERTON END GAME IN TIE, 39-39 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mt. San Antonio scored a touchdown with no time left on the clock, then missed 
the conversion kick as it tied Fullerton College, 39-39, in a nonconference 
game Saturday night at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Tony Campbell caught a 22-yard pass from Cody Smith, but Rodrigo Vera's 
point-after attempt was wide left. 
</P>
<P>
 Marc O'Brien scored on a two-yard bootleg run with 44 seconds left and Tony 
Draft caught a two-point conversion pass from O'Brien, giving Fullerton a 39-33 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton's ensuing squib kick went out of bounds, giving Mt. San Antonio, the 
preseason top-ranked community college team in the nation, the ball on its 35. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Brien completed 17 of 22 passes for 275 yards, with two touchdowns and no 
interceptions in his first college start. 
</P>
<P>
 Freshman Alex Molnar returned a kick 93 yards for a Fullerton touchdown in the 
first half. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonconference games: 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena 27, Orange Coast 25 -- Christian Emerson kicked a 27-yard field goal 
with two seconds remaining to give Pasadena the victory and spoil an Orange 
Coast comeback. 
</P>
<P>
 After trailing, 24-0, at halftime the Pirates scored 25 points, including 19 
in the fourth quarter, capped by a nine-yard run by Jeff Clayton with 3:08 
remaining.  
</P>
<P>
 But a 26-yard pass from Joe Phears to Z Hodges on third and six with less than 
30 seconds remaining set up the game-winning field goal. 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino 55, Rancho Santiago 28 -- Steve Sarkisian threw for 434 yards and 
five touchdowns for El Camino, which passed for 452 yards, the most allowed by 
a Rancho Santiago team. Leandrew Childs had five catches for 146 yards and two 
touchdowns and he scored another touchdown on a 12-yard run for El Camino. 
</P>
<P>
 Ernest Wilson led Rancho Santiago with two touchdowns, one on a 65-yard run 
and the other on a 95-yard kickoff return. 
</P>
<P>
 In the San Diego Mesa water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Grossmont 17, Orange Coast 8 -- Nick Wagner had four goals, Kevin Bobzien and 
David Kasa each had two goals and Kaj Sturdivant recorded six saves for 
visiting Orange Coast (2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Bobzien scored six goals and Kasa added five in the Pirates' 18-4 victory over 
Palomar and Shad Wicker had seven goals and Kasa had added five to lead Orange 
Coast to a 20-5 victory over San Diego Mesa. 
</P>
