<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHAFFEY TAKES WHAT MOORPARK IS GIVING TO GET A 19-13 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM COLEMAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Moorpark College Coach Jim Bittner brought out the shoehorn Saturday night and 
tried to find someone to fill the big cleats of departed stars Todd Preston and 
Gil Carrillo. 
</P>
<P>
 Bittner is still looking for adequate replacements after watching all three of 
his quarterbacks throw interceptions in a 19-13 nonconference loss to Chaffey 
at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither Damian Delfino nor Josh Buck nor Jeremie Watkins seemed to be the 
answer to Preston, All-Western State Conference North Division quarterback last 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Delfino, the starter, completed four of five for 37 yards with an interception 
that Reggie Cornish took 57 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Buck completed four of 13 for 59 yards and his fumble was returned for a 
touchdown. Watkins was three of nine for 31 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Raider running back Corey Bowen wasn't exactly the second coming of Carrillo, 
the two-time All-WSC North Division offensive player of the year. Bowen 
finished with 59 yards in 18 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Yet, Moorpark nearly pulled out a victory, despite making five turnovers and 
allowing four sacks. 
</P>
<P>
 Watkins scored on a one-yard bootleg and Steve Sabbe added the extra point to 
make it 19-13 early in the fourth period. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark got one last chance by blocking Josh Boies' punt. Linebacker Robert 
Webb scooped up the ball and rumbled 28 yards to the Chaffey 13 with 15 seconds 
remaining. A pass-interference penalty moved the ball to the two, and Buck 
tried to scramble into the end zone on the next play but fell a yard short as 
time ran out. 
</P>
<P>
 Chaffey used three big plays -- two of them by the Panther defense -- to take 
a 19-6 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Cornish picked off a Delfino pass and went 57 yards for a touchdown in the 
first quarter, and Thaddeus Variance took a short pass from Zach Brennan and 
raced 63 for a score later in the quarter to give Chaffey a 13-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark cut into the deficit when Delfino connected with Isaiah Mustafa for a 
13-yard touchdown early in the second quarter. The conversion snap foiled the 
extra point attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Chaffey's defense scored again when Buck was sacked and fumbled. Walter 
Williams took the ball and ran 38 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
