</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Call it a measure of revenge. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, Rosamond High found itself trailing L.A. Baptist by 41 points at 
halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 This time around, running back Jamar Day sliced through L.A. Baptist's defense 
for 166 yards in 22 carries and led the Roadrunners to a 12-7 nonleague victory 
Saturday against the defending Southern Section Division X champion in a season 
opener at Alemany High. 
