 It also answered L.A. Baptist's go-ahead touchdown with 2:48 left. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist, which went undefeated in 1993, finished with 60 yards rushing in 
23 carries and 114 yards passing. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite their shortcomings offensively, the Knights almost pulled it out. 
Trailing, 6-0, L.A. Baptist recovered Day's fumble on the Rosamond 19-yard-line 
with under five minutes remaining. Four plays later, Joe Romero barreled into 
the end zone from 11 yards out for a 7-6 lead. 
