<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; LOYOLA BEATS FOUNTAIN VALLEY WITH 3 SCORES IN 5 MINUTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loyola rallied for three touchdowns in the fourth quarter to beat Fountain 
Valley, 21-7, in a nonleague football game Friday at Huntington Beach High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cubs (1-0) scored three touchdowns in a span of just more than five 
minutes in the final quarter to come from behind against the Barons (0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley scored its touchdown when Joey Rozek caught a 25-yard pass 
from quarterback Chris Ponchak with 6:20 left in the third quarter. Ponchak, a 
standout pitcher for Fountain Valley last spring, was 12 for 25 passing for 136 
yards and threw two interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola went up, 14-7, when quarterback Dyle Spielbuhler narrowly avoided a 
sack and then completed a 52-yard touchdown pass to Dan Farmer with 8:30 left 
in the game.  
</P>
<P>
 Spielbuhler was 8 for 16 passing for 120 yards and one interception. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley fumbled on its next possession. Ponchak was hit while 
scrambling and Loyola's Bryan Dunn recovered the ball at the Fountain Valley 
20. 
</P>
<P>
 Four plays later, Mike Vanis scored on a one-yard run off tackle to put the 
Cubs ahead, 21-7. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola tied it, 7-7, on its first possession of the fourth quarter. Mike 
Ellison broke away for a 41-yard scoring run down the left sideline with 11:16 
left in the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The first half featured three missed field goal attempts. Loyola's Mark 
McDonald missed a 32-yard try on the final play of the half. The Cubs 
mishandled the snap on an earlier try. 
</P>
<P>
 Devin O'Day had two interceptions for Fountain Valley. 
</P>
