</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Heidi Siegmund 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ** 1/2 Gravediggaz, "6 Feet Deep," Gee Street/Island. This New York foursome 
is much like Onyx, whose frenetic, testosterone-laden rap breathed new life 
into the genre in '92. "6 Feet Deep" is less explosive than Onyx's album but 
exceptions include such grim raps as "1-800-Suicide" and "Diary of a Madman," 
which push hard-core into an entirely new realm -- call it gore-core. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Heidi Siegmund 
</P>
