<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECORD RACK: IN BRIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Randy Lewis 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ** David Gates, "Love Is Always Seventeen," Discovery. The former Bread head 
is now a cattle rancher, hence the mild country-pop slant to his first album 
since 1980.Hummable melodies still come to Gates as easily as in the '70s; his 
lyrics remain simplistically romantic, as the title suggests. As with Bread, 
Gates' music is more Wonder than manna. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Randy Lewis 
</P>
