<HEADLINE>
<P>
30-YEAR SENTENCE GIVEN IN BIZARRE ABDUCTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was sentenced to 30 years in prison for abducting two women at gunpoint, 
making them buy Twinkie snack cakes and caffeine pills, then forcing them on a 
tour of Christmas lights. 
</P>
<P>
 David Lynn Justice, 21, was sentenced Thursday on aggravated assault charges 
in the December, 1993, abduction of the women outside a Houston restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 Justice told authorities he abducted the women "because he was depressed and 
wanted some company," said prosecutor Debbie Mantooth. He later freed them. 
</P>
