<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUNMEN ROB TOUR BUS BOUND FOR LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three gunmen hijacked a tour bus bound from Monterey Park to Las Vegas on 
Saturday, robbing the tour guide and 40 passengers of more than $20,000, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles County sheriff's spokeswoman Diane Hecht said the gunmen boarded 
the bus at a stop in Rowland Heights on Saturday morning, ordered the driver to 
go to a nearby street and ran away after demanding that the passengers empty 
their wallets and purses. 
</P>
<P>
 One suspect, Yen Chiu, 22, was arrested and held for investigation of robbery 
and kidnaping at the Walnut sheriff's station, Hecht said. Chiu was being held 
on $35,000 bail, deputies said. The other suspects remained at large late 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident occurred after the AA Tour bus stopped in Rowland Heights to pick 
up eight passengers, three of whom turned out to be the robbery suspects. There 
were no reported injuries, Hecht said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
