118 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
RANCHO CUCAMONGA FIRE FULLY CONTAINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Firefighters fully controlled a wildfire Saturday sparked by children playing 
with matches that burned 105 acres in San Bernardino County. 
</P>
<P>
 The blaze near Rancho Cucamonga was contained early Saturday and was fully 
controlled by 6:40 p.m., said Fire Capt. Steve Humeston. 
</P>
<P>
 Two 10-year-old boys admitted setting the fire, officials said. Fire 
investigators may bill the children's parents for the firefighting costs, which 
could run into the thousands of dollars, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The blaze was reported Friday evening on state land covered with shrubs and 
brush. It burned within 200 yards of several expensive homes before fire crews 
and water-dropping aircraft halted the advance, officials said. 
</P>
