<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: SOUTH-CENTRAL; MEETINGS PLANNED ON RIOT DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council 9th District Community Advisory Committee will host two 
meetings this month to begin establishing a redevelopment project for areas 
damaged in the 1992 riots. 
</P>
<P>
 The meetings will begin at 5:45 p.m. Tuesday and Sept. 27 at New Hope Baptist 
Church, 5200 S. Central Ave.Residents, property owners, business people, 
merchants and community leaders are encouraged to attend. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee and Community Redevelopment Agency studied a 5,600-acre area 
bounded by the Santa Monica Freeway on the north, 84th Street on the south, 
Alameda and Central avenues on the east, and roughly Vermont Avenue on the 
west.  
</P>
<P>
 At the meetings, the two agencies will draw boundaries out of the study area 
to draft a preliminary plan for redevelopment. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 977-1707. 
</P>
</TEXT>
