<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: SOUTH GATE; L.A. PHILHARMONIC OFFERS FREE CONCERT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Philharmonic will stage a free concert at 7 p.m. Sept. 30 in 
the South Gate Municipal Auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
 The evening's program will feature Latin music by composers Aaron Copland, 
Ralph Vaughan Williams, Manuel de Falla and Alberto Ginastera. Grant Gershon 
will conduct the performance, which will feature mezzo-soprano Carmella Jones. 
</P>
<P>
 The concert, one in the city's Neighborhood Concerts series, is free, but 
tickets are required and can be reserved by calling in advance. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 563-5443. 
</P>
