COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: EL SERENO; COMPOSER ILLUSTRATES MUSIC THROUGH TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The El Sereno Branch Library will host musician and composer Jim McAuley, who 
uses instruments to illustrate changes in music through four centuries, in a 
free performance Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Guitar from Renaissance to Rap" begins at 3:30 p.m. at the library, 4990 
Huntington Drive South.  
</P>
<P>
 McAuley has worked with Frank Sinatra and mime Marcel Marceau and has recorded 
here and abroad with his own groups. He encourages active audience 
participation as he shows the progression of American music from blues to rock 
and jazz. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is open to the public. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 225-9201. 
