<TEXT>
<P>
 The West Adams Heritage Assn. is organizing residents to participate in the 
10th annual walkathon Sept. 25 benefiting AIDS Project Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 This will be the first year that the residents association will have a team in 
the 10-kilometer walk. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants are encouraged to register now to receive a sponsor form and 
information. Sponsors who pledge $1 a kilometer, for example, would pay $10. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration for the walk is 9 a.m. Sept. 25. The opening ceremony is at 9:30 
a.m., and the walk begins at 10 a.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Information: Natalie Neith, (213) 731-0042, or the AIDS Walk office, (213) 
466-WALK. 
