<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Anti-abortion stance -- An Aug. 10 article in The Times incorrectly implied 
that Rep. Robert K. Dornan (R-Garden Grove) and a few other conservative 
Republicans in Congress support the killing of abortion doctors by 
anti-abortion extremists. Dornan is a supporter of anti-abortion groups such as 
Operation Rescue but he opposes the use of violence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Correction 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA091194-0458 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 078319 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
September 11, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Magazine; Page 8; Magazine Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
24 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In "Small Worlds" (Kids' Style, Aug. 21), the photo of a multipurpose room at 
the Warner Bros. day-care center was taken by Hewitt/Garrison. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Correction 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
